    "body": "When Cython analyses type annotation containing `cython.XYZ[...]` (`cython.const[]`, `cython.pointer[]`) it tries to look up Cython scope to find type matching `XYZ` name. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/62a4106657b31485aed27ecdc42c68012b02cd8c/Cython/Compiler/ExprNodes.py#L4188\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/62a4106657b31485aed27ecdc42c68012b02cd8c/Cython/Compiler/ExprNodes.py#L7962\r\n\r\nThere is no such type (`const`, `pointer`) hence Cython initializes CythonScope which ends up loading memoryview utility code.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/62a4106657b31485aed27ecdc42c68012b02cd8c/Cython/Compiler/CythonScope.py#L55\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/62a4106657b31485aed27ecdc42c68012b02cd8c/Cython/Compiler/CythonScope.py#L136\r\n\r\nThis PR simply detects Cython scope valid attributes which occurs in type definition but are not type itself and just returns expected `None` without loading Cython scope.\r\n\r\nCloses #7487",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
